comments.body:
csiMountMgr#SetUpAt appears to do a list:
```go
//TODO (vladimirvivien) consider using VolumesAttachments().Get() to retrieve
//the object directly. This requires the ability to reconstruct the ID using volumeName+nodeName (nodename may not be avilable)
attachList, err := c.k8s.StorageV1alpha1().VolumeAttachments().List(meta.ListOptions{})
```

listing all storage objects isn't something nodes can do today. to get a particular VolumeAttachment, it looks like both the kubelet and the node authorizer would need to re-derive the VolumeAttachment name, presumably using this approach:
```go
func getAttachmentName(volName, nodeName string) string {
	// TODO consider using a different prefix for attachment
	return fmt.Sprintf("pv-%s", hashAttachmentName(volName, nodeName))
}
```

is that name generation finalized and stable? once we have existent VolumeAttachment objects, we won't be able to easily change the naming scheme.

